# Skill Search & Stack Builder

A local-first web MVP for searching and understanding 631+ skills with an exportable recommended stack.

## Features

✅ **Local-First** - No external services required
✅ **Full-Text Search** - SQLite FTS5 with BM25 ranking
✅ **Smart Filters** - Category, tags, and enriched cards
✅ **Skill Cards** - Editable metadata (use when, avoid when, risk level, etc.)
✅ **Stack Builder** - Select, reorder, and export skills
✅ **Export** - Markdown or JSON format
✅ **Explainability** - See matched fields and BM25 scores

## Tech Stack

- **Frontend**: Next.js 15 (App Router) + React 19 + Tailwind CSS
- **Backend**: Next.js API Routes
- **Database**: SQLite with FTS5 (better-sqlite3)
- **Language**: TypeScript

## Quick Start

### 1. Install Dependencies

```bash
npm install
```

### 2. Initialize Database

This parses `CATALOG.md` and creates the SQLite database with FTS index:

```bash
npm run init-db
```

Expected output:
```
🚀 Initializing database...
📋 Copying CATALOG.md to data directory...
📊 Creating database schema...
📖 Parsing CATALOG.md...
✅ Parsed 631 skills
💾 Inserting skills into database...
✅ Inserted 631 skills
✅ FTS index contains 631 entries
🎉 Database initialization complete!
```

### 3. Run Development Server

```bash
npm run dev
```

Open [http://localhost:3000](http://localhost:3000) in your browser.

